<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
A description of the source can be added, if clarity is needed, at the end of the Works Cited entry. 
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author. <em>Title</em>. Name of website, date video was posted, URL. Description. 
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Norton, R.</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Title"><em>How to train a Cat to Operate a Light Switch</em></span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Name of website">Youtube</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Date">4 Nov. 2006</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="URL">www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vja83KLQXZs</span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Description">Online video</span>.
</blockquote>
<br><br>
