<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
When you use another person&#8217;s ideas in your writing, list the author&#8217;s name, in parentheses, immediately following the cited material. 
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Training a cat requires&hellip; (Norton). 
</blockquote>
<br><br>
Or include the author&#8217;s name in your sentence.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In the video posted to YouTube, Norton showed that a cat can be trained&hellip;
</blockquote>
